<Page title="Privacy — Osprey" description="How Osprey handles your data.">
  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p>Last Updated: July 2, 2026</p>

  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>OSPREY ("we," "us," "our," or "the App") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application and related services.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

  <h3>1.1 HealthKit Data</h3>
  <p>With your explicit permission, OSPREY accesses your Apple HealthKit data to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Read workout data (distance, duration, calories, heart rate, elevation)</li>
    <li>Read dietary data (food logs, water intake)</li>
    <li>Read body measurements (weight, body fat percentage)</li>
    <li>Write workout summaries and recovery metrics back to HealthKit</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>We do not share HealthKit data with third parties.</strong> You can revoke HealthKit access at any time through your iOS Settings &gt; Health &gt; Data Access & Devices &gt; OSPREY.</p>

  <h3>1.2 Location Data</h3>
  <p>With your permission, OSPREY collects GPS location data to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Track running, cycling, and outdoor activity routes</li>
    <li>Calculate distance and map visualization</li>
    <li>Support race event location features</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Location data is encrypted and stored on our secure servers. You can disable location collection at any time through iOS Settings &gt; Privacy &gt; Location Services.</p>

  <h3>1.3 Account Information</h3>
  <p>When you create an OSPREY account, we collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Display name</li>
    <li>Profile information (goals, preferences, training style)</li>
    <li>Authentication credentials (managed securely by Supabase)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>1.4 Usage Data</h3>
  <p>We automatically collect non-personal usage data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>App crashes and performance metrics</li>
    <li>Feature usage patterns</li>
    <li>Device model and iOS version</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <p>We use collected information for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Providing and improving OSPREY features</li>
    <li>Personalizing your training plans and recommendations</li>
    <li>Enabling social features (friends, challenges, race events)</li>
    <li>Processing in-app purchases and subscriptions</li>
    <li>Sending push notifications related to your workouts and goals (with your consent)</li>
    <li>Diagnosing technical issues and improving app performance</li>
    <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Third-Party Service Providers</h2>
  <p>OSPREY uses the following third-party services to operate. These providers process data under strict data processing agreements:</p>

  <h3>3.1 Supabase (Backend & Database)</h3>
  <p>We use Supabase for secure data storage, authentication, and API infrastructure. Supabase may access encrypted user data only to the extent necessary to provide database services. <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Supabase Privacy Policy</a></p>

  <h3>3.2 OpenAI (AI-Powered Training Plans)</h3>
  <p>OSPREY uses OpenAI's API to generate personalized training recommendations based on your fitness data. OpenAI processes data only to fulfill API requests and does not use it to train models. <a href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenAI Privacy Policy</a></p>

  <h3>3.3 ElevenLabs (Voice Features)</h3>
  <p>We use ElevenLabs for text-to-speech voice feedback during workouts. Voice processing occurs on their secure servers. <a href="https://elevenlabs.io/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ElevenLabs Privacy Policy</a></p>

  <h3>3.4 RevenueCat (Subscription Management)</h3>
  <p>OSPREY uses RevenueCat to process in-app purchases and manage subscriptions. RevenueCat handles billing and entitlements securely. <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">RevenueCat Privacy Policy</a></p>

  <h3>3.5 Apple App Store Connect & TestFlight</h3>
  <p>Crash logs and performance data may be collected by Apple. <a href="https://www.apple.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple Privacy Policy</a></p>

  <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
  <p>We implement industry-standard security measures:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>End-to-end encryption for sensitive data in transit</li>
    <li>Database encryption at rest (Supabase)</li>
    <li>Row-level security policies enforcing user-only data access</li>
    <li>Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</li>
    <li>No password storage (OAuth-based authentication where possible)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Despite our efforts, no security system is impenetrable. We cannot guarantee absolute security of your data.</p>

  <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Workout & Health Data:</strong> Retained indefinitely or until you request deletion</li>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Retained while your account is active; deleted 90 days after account deletion</li>
    <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> Retained with your workout logs; can be deleted with workout records</li>
    <li><strong>Crash/Performance Logs:</strong> Retained for 30 days for debugging purposes</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access your personal data</li>
    <li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li>
    <li>Opt out of marketing communications</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent for data processing</li>
    <li>Request a copy of your data in portable format</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise these rights, contact us using the information below.</p>

  <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>OSPREY is not directed to users under 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will promptly delete such information.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the new policy in the app or sending a notification. Your continued use of OSPREY constitutes your acceptance of any changes.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:</p>
  <p><strong>Email:</strong> Thunderbob34@gmail.com</p>
  <p><strong>App Support:</strong> In-app support form or Settings &gt; Help & Support</p>

  <p>© 2026 OSPREY. All rights reserved.</p>
</Page>
